Webcal protocol ({{webcall://}}) should be supported by Team Calendars. Currently, changing the {{webcal://}} to {{http://}} is the workaround

h4. Steps to Reproduce
Subscribe to this calendar: {{webcal://www.studiosdigital.at/sites/default/files/downloads/blog/deutsche-feiertage-2013.ics}}

This is what we get:
!screenshot000.jpg!

Changing the {{webcal}} to {{http}} will work

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-50084].
  {panel}

All the links in the top bar of Confluence have the parameter id defined. For example:
{noformat}<a id="people-directory-link" href="/peopledirectory.action" class=" aui-nav-imagelink" title="People">
            <span>People</span>
    </a>{noformat}

Team calendars add a button to that bar but no id is defined for it:
{noformat}<a href="/calendar/mycalendar.action" class=" aui-nav-imagelink" title="Calendars">
            <span>Calendars</span>
    </a>{noformat}

This make more difficult to apply CSS customization to that item.

+Workaround:+

You can use the href property to apply CSS to that button:
{code}a[href='/calendar/mycalendar.action']{
   your css code here
}{code}

