So the problem is in Personal calendar which shows nothing but 504 error from web-server after user tries to open it for the first time.
This behavior are started after the Confluence relocation to virtual environment, so problem obviously related to performance (low loaded clone instance of Confluence works fine with first start of personal Calendar), but maybe you can suggest some workarounds (except increasing the timeout, because now it's already 90sec)? All Confluence and other plugin's functionality is fine, but lack of Team Calendars for our new users (about 10-20 each weak) is very frustrating.

